<br>
Because VI put mobs in the game with a gazillion HP and made those mobs MR.  <br>
<br>
VI's solution to a problem THEY created by creating these mobs is to dilute the classes to the point where each one is indistinguishable from the next.  <br>
<br>
VI raised the level cap to 60, without really very much thought to how each class would be utilised at the next level.  Vox and Naggy are trivial???  WTF?  How did this happen?  Lets put a level cap on em.  Greater heal isn't a sufficient heal for druids at level 60????  How did we miss that one?  Better fix it!  Wizards are inneffective post 50?  Better give them lures!  Rangers defensive skills are inneffective against level 60 mobs????  OMG?  How did this happen?  Better fix it!  Rogues do so much more damage then any other class that they are gettign stomped into the ground???  Give em evade!  Druids still aren't fixed?  Sheesh, clerics seem to be doing alright, lets give them cleric sorts of spells!  Pally's and SK's aren't being fully utilized on raids???  Lets give them better tanking abilities and higher damage output!<br>
<br>
Clerics and Warriors complain that they are being marginalised????  C'mon guys, simmer down there!  You are the two most necessary classes in the game with these uber mobs we created.  We can't give you any additional effective skills because you completely OWN those L33T raid mobs that the very top tier guilds are fighting.  Clerics are really upset?  Ok, ok, look, we weren't going to tell you this just yet, but we were all along going to make you mini-paladins, so sorry not to come out with it in the first place, we just figured that you would understand, given how we fixed Ragefire for you by making the quest no longer linear, putting Rage in Skyfire and making Ragefire spawn once a week instead of once every couple days.  Don't you trust us???  <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :p --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/tongue.gif ALT=":p"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END--> <br>
